"{Natsume}\n"
"\"......Mhmm.\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:114
msgid ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"Good, I'm glad.\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:115
msgid "I felt relieved to finally give her the gift, and by the fact that she actually liked it."
msgstr ""

#: 40304:116
msgid "I couldn't give it to her for a while, and it was my first time giving a girl a present. Well, OK, I tried forcing one on a girl in the past, and she ran away."
msgstr ""

#: 40304:117
msgid "I felt like I really had saved her at last."
msgstr ""

#: 40304:118
msgid ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"Oh yeah. Miya-san picked it out for you. He thought you'd like that design.\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:121
msgid "Natsume-chan looked surprised as I said that."
msgstr ""

#: 40304:122
msgid ""
"{Natsume}\n"
"\"Papa remembered what I like?\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:123
msgid ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"Sure. He's your dad. I'm sure he never forgot about you.\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:126
msgid ""
"{Natsume}\n"
"\"I doubt that. He's an alchemaniac.\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:132
msgid ""
"{Mizuki}\n"
"\"An alchemaniac...\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:133
msgid ""
"{Ran}\n"
"\"Ptt...!\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:134
msgid "It didn't sound like she was talking about her own father, and everyone was trying not to laugh about it. I wished I could have laughed out loud, too."
msgstr ""

#: 40304:135
msgid "I was just overjoyed to have her back."
msgstr ""

#: 40304:140
msgid ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"Oh yeah, are you going to live with your dad?\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:141
msgid "Unlike the rest of us, Natsume-chan now had family living on the island."
msgstr ""

#: 40304:142
msgid "I'm sure she wants to live with him, to make up for lost time."
msgstr ""

#: 40304:145
msgid ""
"{Natsume}\n"
"\"But I'm going to be coming to this school starting next semester. I'm on full scholarship. V.\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:146
msgid "She made a peace sign with her hand. I guess the principal decided on that. Why did she do that?"
msgstr ""

#: 40304:149
msgid ""
"{Natsume}\n"
"\"Isn't this a boarding school? That means I'm supposed to be living in the dorm.\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:155
msgid ""
"{Haruka}\n"
"\"I'm sure it doesn't matter. That's kind of weird coming from me, though.\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:156
msgid ""
"{Mizuki}\n"
"\"I'm sure it's fine if Haruka says so. Don't you think Miya-san will miss you if you live here?\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:161
msgid ""
"{Natsume}\n"
"\"I don't care about that. He didn't come to get me for a long time. I'm going to spend a night at his place tonight, but I'll be living here starting tomorrow.\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:162
msgid ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"So, you're going to Miya-san's tonight.\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:163
msgid "Then I'm sure Miya-san was getting ready for her to come home by now. I could easily imagine him doing that, and it made me smile."
msgstr ""

#: 40304:166
msgid ""
"{Natsume}\n"
"\"Just for tonight. I'll be back by tomorrow afternoon.\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:167
msgid ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"You're already talking about when you'll get back? You're way too rushed.\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:168
msgid ""
"Natsume-chan looked up at me.\n"
"I'm not sure, but I think she's glaring at me."
msgstr ""

#: 40304:171
msgid ""
"{Natsume}\n"
"\"Haruma, is it somehow inconvenient for you if I stay here?\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:172
msgid ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"No, not at all. But it's been such a long time since you've spent time with your dad, I was thinking you should spend more time together.\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:175
msgid ""
"{Natsume}\n"
"\"......\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:176
msgid ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"Why are you looking like a blowfish?\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:179
msgid ""
"{Natsume}\n"
"\"Who's a blowfish? If I'm a blowfish, then Suzu's a pig.\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:184
msgid ""
"{Rin}\n"
"\"Umm... am I that fat?\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:188
msgid ""
"{Pierre}\n"
"\"Regardless of the truth, it seems like you're stuck as 'the fatty' in Natsume-chan's mind.\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:189
msgid ""
"{Rin}\n"
"\"That blows...\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:193
msgid ""
"{Natsume}\n"
"\"Suzu has a big butt.\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:194
msgid ""
"{Rin}\n"
"\"Hhh?!\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:195
msgid "Fujisaki-san was mortified by Natsume-chan's verbal abuse."
msgstr ""

#: 40304:196
msgid ""
"{Rin}\n"
"\"I give up. I must come from the planet of the fat people. I'm going back to my own people, now...\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:200
msgid ""
"{Mizuki}\n"
"\"Hey, Rin's losing it...\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:201
msgid ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"Quit bashing Fujisaki-san. I don't know why, but you're just taking things out on her, right?\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:206
msgid ""
"{Natsume}\n"
"\"Grr... You're so boring.\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:207
msgid "She wolfed down her dinner in a bad mood, but she was using the chopsticks I gave her."
msgstr ""

#: 40304:210
msgid ""
"{Natsume}\n"
"\"I'm going home when I finish this.\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:211
msgid ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"You should. I'll walk you home.\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:214
msgid ""
"{Natsume}\n"
"\"... Fine. *Omnomnomnomnom.*\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:221
msgid "You could hear the insects chirping as we walked."
msgstr ""

#: 40304:224
msgid ""
"{Natsume}\n"
"\"Listen to this. It's a tunnel of bugs.\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:225
msgid "I heard her footsteps close behind me amidst the loud chorus of bugs."
msgstr ""

#: 40304:226
msgid ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"A tunnel of bugs, huh.\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:227
msgid "I thought it was a great expression. I felt we were surrounded by the sound of insects, and it really was like a tunnel."
msgstr ""

#: 40304:228
msgid "I felt emotional, walking with her under the stars, surrounded by the sound of bugs."
msgstr ""

#: 40304:229
msgid ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"I'm really happy to be able to walk with you like this.\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:232
msgid ""
"{Natsume}\n"
"\"You are...\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:234
msgid "She mumbled, and looked down at her feet. She was already walking slower than I was, so that made her fall further behind."
msgstr ""

#: 40304:236
msgid "I had gotten pretty far ahead of her, so I stopped to wait for her. I reached out my hand to Natsume-chan as she caught up with me, but she looked down."
msgstr ""

#: 40304:239
msgid ""
"{Natsume}\n"
"\"Aren't you scared of me, Haruma?\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:240
msgid "She asked, looking at my hand."
msgstr ""

#: 40304:241
msgid ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"Why would I be scared? Why are you worried about that?\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:244
msgid ""
"{Natsume}\n"
"\"Didn't you hear about it from Papa?\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:245
msgid "This must be about the stone inside of her. Could it be that Natsume-chan was scared as well?"
msgstr ""

#: 40304:246
msgid ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"I'm sure you'll be fine.\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:247
msgid "I took her hand in mine since she just kept staring at it."
msgstr ""

#: 40304:248
msgid "I don't know much, but I feel like I can be a big help to her because of that."
msgstr ""

#: 40304:249
msgid "That's why I should be on her side from now on. I'll blow away whatever fears she has and share my happiness with her."
msgstr ""

#: 40304:250
msgid ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"Don't worry. Everything's gonna turn out fine.\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:253
msgid ""
"{Natsume}\n"
"\"...... OK.\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:254
msgid "She faintly gripped my hand back."
msgstr ""

#: 40304:255
msgid ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"You got Miya-san on your side as well. He's an alchemaniac, right? In that case, he'll be able to do something about that.\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:258
msgid ""
"{Natsume}\n"
"\"You're right. That's the only thing he's good at.\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:259
msgid ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"See? I'm here too. You'll be just fine.\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:262
msgid ""
"{Natsume}\n"
"\"You're even more useless, Haruma.\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:263
msgid ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"That I am!\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:266
msgid ""
"{Natsume}\n"
"\"Don't be so proud of it.\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:267
msgid "Natsume-chan smiled. I smiled as well, so that she could keep on smiling."
msgstr ""

#: 40304:268
msgid "I think that's the key for us. That's how I felt."
msgstr ""

#: 40304:275
msgid ""
"{Amamiya}\n"
"\"Here you go. Would you like some tea?\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:276
msgid "He put a cup of hot tea in front of me. This was my first time being in his house like this."
msgstr ""

#: 40304:277
msgid ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"Thank you. But, I'll be leaving soon.\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:278
msgid "I just walked her home. I shouldn't be spoiling the family reunion by staying too long."
msgstr ""

#: 40304:282
msgid ""
"{Natsume}\n"
"\"Don't worry. It's the cheap stuff, but enjoy yourself anyway.\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:286
msgid ""
"{Amamiya}\n"
"\"Yes, yes, stay as long as you want. I want to talk to you about something, as well.\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:287
msgid ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"Talk about what?\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:290
msgid ""
"{Amamiya}\n"
"\"I want to ask you and Natsume about something.\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:291
msgid "I noticed the change in his eyes. It seemed to be something very important."
msgstr ""

#: 40304:292
msgid ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"OK, so I guess I'll stay a while.\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:293
msgid "If that's the case, then I should stay. I'll listen as I enjoy the tea."
msgstr ""

#: 40304:298
msgid ""
"{Amamiya}\n"
"\"It was just like this island, but there wasn't anybody there?\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:299
msgid "Miya-san was talking about the place where Natsume-chan was. He said the only people who knew about that place were Natsume-chan and I."
msgstr ""

#: 40304:300
msgid ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"You don't know about that place either, Miya-san?\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:303
msgid ""
"{Amamiya}\n"
"\"I've caught glimpses. Any competent alchemist should be able to feel the existence of a world that is not our own.\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:304
msgid ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"Really?\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:307
msgid ""
"{Amamiya}\n"
"\"But it was only for a moment. I couldn't stay long enough to truly recognize that world.\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:308
msgid ""
"{Amamiya}\n"
"\"Let alone for me to become assimilated into that world like you and Natsume-chan were. Only a handful of chosen people can do that.\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:309
msgid ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"Really? But...\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:310
msgid "I thought I understood, but then I got confused right away. Why was I able to find Natsume-chan in that world?"
msgstr ""

#: 40304:314
msgid ""
"{Natsume}\n"
"\"You entered through your dreams.\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:315
msgid "Natsume-chan interrupted me. I thought she was right."
msgstr ""

#: 40304:316
msgid ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"Well, it was a dream to me. Was it not a dream?\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:317
msgid "I thought I didn't remember it because it was a dream. After all, you usually forget what you dreamed about, and only thing you remember is the fuzzy surface of the dream."
msgstr ""

#: 40304:321
msgid ""
"{Amamiya}\n"
"\"Dreams are a common entrance into the other world. Anyone pursuing our line of work has experienced it to some extent.\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:322
msgid ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"Really? But... I'm Joe Normal.\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:323
msgid "I'd never heard of anything like that, and I couldn't believe something like that happened all the time."
msgstr ""

#: 40304:324
msgid ""
"{Amamiya}\n"
"\"Haruma-kun, have you had any experience with magic?\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:325
msgid ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"No, not at all. I don't know much about alchemy, either.\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:328
msgid ""
"{Amamiya}\n"
"\"I see. Then...\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:333
msgid ""
"{Natsume}\n"
"\"Haruma has a huge furnace inside of him.\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:334
msgid "Natsume-chan said something entirely incomprehensible."
msgstr ""

#: 40304:335
msgid ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"Me? A furnace?\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:336
msgid "Natsume-chan pointed at my stomach... Wait, I've got an alchemy furnace in my stomach?!"
msgstr ""

#: 40304:339
msgid ""
"{Amamiya}\n"
"\"I see. Haruma-kun, do you have more vigor than most other people?\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:340
msgid ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"Huh? Uh, don't know? But this isn't really the place to...\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:341
msgid "Why would he say that in front of Natsume-chan?"
msgstr ""

#: 40304:344
msgid ""
"{Natsume}\n"
"\"You're boundless, huh?\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:345
msgid "I guess she didn't really care."
msgstr ""

#: 40304:346
msgid ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"I guess I may be more active than other guys...\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:347
msgid "What are we talking about? I was embarrassed, and my face was turning red."
msgstr ""

#: 40304:351
msgid ""
"{Amamiya}\n"
"\"They say 'Heroes enjoy the pleasures of the flesh'. The great men who made their mark on history were often unrivaled by others in their desires. That vitality is one kind of talent.\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:353
msgid ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"Huh, is it?\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:354
msgid "It sounded like an embarrassing talent."
msgstr ""

#: 40304:358
msgid ""
"{Amamiya}\n"
"\"It is genuine talent. Some people use that vitality to pursue something similar to what alchemy does.\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:359
msgid ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"It's like what alchemists make...? You mean gold?\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:360
msgid ""
"{Amamiya}\n"
"\"Yes. It does have gold in its name in face. The Golden Elixir.\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:361
msgid ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"Golden Elixir?\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:362
msgid "I'd never heard of that."
msgstr ""

#: 40304:364
msgid ""
"{Amamiya}\n"
"\"Alchemy is the practice of creating chemicals to turn base metals into gold. We heat the ingredients for an extended period of time forcing them to change and create a new substance.\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:366
msgid ""
"{Amamiya}\n"
"\"Some people do this within their own body. Such as the Neidan school of Chinese Alchemy taught by Taoism.\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:367
msgid ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"Within their own body? Wow...\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:368
msgid ""
"{Amamiya}\n"
"\"The container is the philosopher, and his embryo is his body. The ingredients to use are the natural chi in the air, and the burner is the point below his navel.\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:369
msgid ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"Uh-huh...\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:370
msgid "Sorry man, I didn't get a frickin' word of that. Miya-san caught on, and smiled wryly."
msgstr ""

#: 40304:374
msgid ""
"{Amamiya}\n"
"\"Let's just keep it at that. What it means is that Haruma-kun is full of energy, and when you have more energy, your dreams become more vivid, and seem much more real, don't they?\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:376
msgid ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"Oh, yeah. My dreams are always in really bright colors.\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:377
msgid "Some people say their dreams are in black and white, but I couldn't imagine that."
msgstr ""

#: 40304:378
msgid ""
"{Amamiya}\n"
"\"The more real your dreams get, the less different they are from reality, and once they cross the line, they become another reality.\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:379
msgid ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"So, I crossed that line?\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:381
msgid "I guess that's why I wandered into the world where Natsume-chan was contained: the entrance to that world was my dream. I'm still not sure, but I'll just let it rest for now."
msgstr ""

#: 40304:383
msgid ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"So, what is that world, anyways?\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:384
msgid "Well, let's say that world existed, but we aren't sure what that is."
msgstr ""

#: 40304:388
msgid ""
"{Natsume}\n"
"\"That world is made from human desires.\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:389
msgid "Natsume-chan was looking at the ceiling, and started to talk like she was trying to remember it."
msgstr ""

#: 40304:390
msgid ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"Made from human desires?\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:391
msgid ""
"{Natsume}\n"
"\"There is no time in that world. Everything is so calm, so quiet. Maybe it's the ideal world.\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:396
msgid ""
"{Amamiya}\n"
"\"The ideal world...?\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:400
msgid ""
"{Natsume}\n"
"\"A quiet place with no war. There is no time, so nothing ever dies. Whatever's in that world will live forever.\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:401
msgid ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"That's an ideal?\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:402
msgid "I couldn't agree with that, because that world sounded too lonely."
msgstr ""

#: 40304:403
msgid "If it was a real utopia, I probably wouldn't have thought of taking Natsume-chan away from there."
msgstr ""

#: 40304:407
msgid ""
"{Amamiya}\n"
"\"An eternal world, huh. It is a never ending dream of mankind to overcome death.\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:408
msgid ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"But...\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:411
msgid ""
"{Amamiya}\n"
"\"Maybe it's the profound, elegant world where enlightened high priests and monks go.\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:412
msgid "Could that really be where they end up?"
msgstr ""

#: 40304:413
msgid ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"Maybe those enlightened people don't feel the loneliness.\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:414
msgid "If not being lonely in that kind of place is required to be a better person, then maybe I don't want to be a better person."
msgstr ""

#: 40304:415
msgid ""
"{Amamiya}\n"
"\"What do you think, Natsume?\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:419
msgid ""
"{Natsume}\n"
"\"I don't like that place either. It's a crooked world.\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:420
msgid ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"A crooked world?\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:423
msgid ""
"{Natsume}\n"
"\"It's an 'ideal' world created by the never ending desires of man. Mankind has always been quite afraid of death. Many people have sought immortality.\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:424
msgid ""
"{Natsume}\n"
"\"Those thoughts, wishes, and hopes gathered together and created that world. The thoughts of people made that timeless, 'ideal' world.\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:427
msgid ""
"{Natsume}\n"
"\"And it was just one of them. I think there must be other places like that elsewhere.\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:428
msgid ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"That's not the only one?\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:432
msgid ""
"{Amamiya}\n"
"\"I've heard the best alchemists can create a small universe artificially, just like this one.\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:433
msgid ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"They can make entire universes?\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:434
msgid "That was way over my head. I thought I was going to faint."
msgstr ""

#: 40304:438
msgid ""
"{Natsume}\n"
"\"The stone inside of me reacts to that world. That world is connected to the stone.\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:439
msgid ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"Connected?\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:444
msgid ""
"{Amamiya}\n"
"\"I see. Maybe that world is the power source for the alchemy on this island?\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:445
msgid "Natsume-chan nodded. I had no idea, but Miya-san seemed to understand that."
msgstr ""

#: 40304:449
msgid ""
"{Amamiya}\n"
"\"I'll explain it to you.\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:450
msgid "Miya-san said."
msgstr ""

#: 40304:453
msgid ""
"{Amamiya}\n"
"\"The alchemy on this island has the power to refine materials to a higher state. Take this knife, for example...\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:454
msgid "Miya-san took the fruit knife he used to peel a peach a little while ago."
msgstr ""

#: 40304:455
msgid ""
"{Amamiya}\n"
"\"Let's say that we change this knife with alchemy. Then it'll cut better than a usual knife. This is because the object can make use of its properties to perfection.\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:456
msgid ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"I can understand that, kind of.\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:457
msgid "If you refine a knife, then it'll cut better, and refining oil will make it burn longer."
msgstr ""

#: 40304:458
msgid ""
"{Amamiya}\n"
"\"Then, why does it happen? What do you think, Haruma-kun?\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:459
msgid "He asked me like a teacher."
msgstr ""

#: 40304:460
msgid ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"Well... Because alchemy changes the materials? I guess?\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:461
msgid "I don't know how the changes worked, and I was certain it all depended on the materials. So that's all I could say about it."
msgstr ""

#: 40304:464
msgid ""
"{Amamiya}\n"
"\"That's one way to think of it. One can also think of it this way.\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:465
msgid "Miya-san smiled."
msgstr ""

#: 40304:468
msgid ""
"{Amamiya}\n"
"\"The reason why this knife cuts better is because this knife was switched with a better knife right in front of you.\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:469
msgid ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"What? It was switched?\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:470
msgid "I thought I got it, but then I was confused again."
msgstr ""

#: 40304:471
msgid ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"You said switched. But, what and what?\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:475
msgid ""
"{Natsume}\n"
"\"Haruma, you're an idiot. The regular knife was replaced with the better one of course.\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:476
msgid ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"Oh, I see. No! Where did this better knife come from?\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:477
msgid "There was only one knife there, and there weren't any other knives around there to be switched with."
msgstr ""

#: 40304:482
msgid ""
"{Amamiya}\n"
"\"That's what we're telling you.\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:483
msgid ""
"{Natsume}\n"
"\"It's there.\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:484
msgid ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"There? Oh, there?\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:485
msgid "In the place where Natsume-chan was? That empty world? And the better knife was in that world and it was switched with this knife?"
msgstr ""

#: 40304:488
msgid ""
"{Amamiya}\n"
"\"In other words, this island's alchemy is the task of using a catalyst to extract the ideal objects born upon that 'ideal world' where Natsume-chan was.\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:491
msgid ""
"{Amamiya}\n"
"\"The stone inside of Natsume was created using that world's power. I'm sure there's still some link to it left inside.\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:492
msgid ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"Uhh...\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:493
msgid "I stopped thinking."
msgstr ""

#: 40304:496
msgid ""
"{Natsume}\n"
"\"Look, let's say that we successfully made something like the Philosopher's Stone with alchemy. That would be a piece of that world's power.\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:497
msgid ""
"{Natsume}\n"
"\"Now let's say that's this tea. Then, for example, we sprinkle this tea onto the knife.\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:498
msgid "She sprinkled the tea onto the fruit knife."
msgstr ""

#: 40304:499
msgid ""
"{Natsume}\n"
"\"This makes the knife connected to that world, because this tea is a product from it. Now it creates a connection between the two worlds.\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:502
msgid ""
"{Natsume}\n"
"\"That connection causes this knife's twin to be born on that world. Though it is a twin, its nature is completely different, and the knife on that world is the ideal form.\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:503
msgid ""
"{Natsume}\n"
"\"When you have a good knife and a bad knife, then the good knife will remain.\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:504
msgid "And so the better knife remains in your hand, huh?"
msgstr ""

#: 40304:505
msgid "Two knives. Two worlds."
msgstr ""

#: 40304:506
msgid ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"A light and a shadow...\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:507
msgid ""
"{Amamiya}\n"
"\"The idea that this world is composed of yin and yang, male and female principals existing in opposition... This is an idea shared by alchemists as well.\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:508
msgid ""
"{Amamiya}\n"
"\"The union of male and female is one of the ultimate themes of alchemy.\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:511
msgid ""
"{Amamiya}\n"
"\"The hermaphrodite is thought to be sacred because they have unified male and female within their own body.\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:512
msgid ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"What's hermaphrodite mean? A guy with two swords?\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:515
msgid ""
"{Natsume}\n"
"\"What?! Miyamoto Musashi was a homo? Then was Musashi x Kojiro possible?\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:516
msgid ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"Who knows?\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:519
msgid ""
"{Amamiya}\n"
"\"Umm, I think you're getting off topic... No, not a man with two of them, a hermaphrodite - someone who has both male and female sex organs.\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:520
msgid ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"Oh, I see.\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:521
msgid "I guess I understand. So, it's a person who has a dick and a pussy."
msgstr ""

#: 40304:522
msgid "I guess they're getting a two for one deal on that?"
msgstr ""

#: 40304:525
msgid ""
"{Amamiya}\n"
"\"See? I'm sure you know, but angels are sexless, right? It's the same reason behind that. By being neither sex, they are also both.\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:526
msgid ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"No, I didn't know that.\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:529
msgid ""
"{Amamiya}\n"
"\"Oh, I see.\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:532
msgid ""
"{Natsume}\n"
"\"Don't expect anything from Haruma.\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:533
msgid "She said it as an insult, but she was right. I was getting so confused by the conversation we were having."
msgstr ""

#: 40304:534
msgid ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"So the alchemy we're doing borrows its power from the world Natsume-chan was in?\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:537
msgid ""
"{Amamiya}\n"
"\"If you put it in the simplest terms possible, yes. It's the act of trying to connect this world and that world.\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:540
msgid ""
"{Amamiya}\n"
"\"It only happens in a limited space, but those two worlds do connect for a second and mix. You could say it's like crossbreeding worlds.\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:541
msgid ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"Crossbreeding worlds?\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:542
msgid "They're saying that alchemists pull mysterious stuff out of that place? I am so fucking lost right now..."
msgstr ""

#: 40304:545
msgid ""
"{Natsume}\n"
"\"That's why I noticed Hisae's experiment. Any alchemy performed on this world is easily noticeable on that world.\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:546
msgid ""
"{Natsume}\n"
"\"I didn't like it, so I interfered. It was all under the right conditions, anyway.\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:547
msgid "Is that the experiment when we were guarding the furnace for the principal? The first time Natsume-chan came over to this world?"
msgstr ""

#: 40304:548
msgid ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"What was that all about too? Who was that Natsume-chan?\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:549
msgid "Natsume-chan was banished by the principal. The principal said Natsume-chan was neither a human being, nor a homunculus, but something like a shadow."
msgstr ""

#: 40304:552
msgid ""
"{Natsume}\n"
"\"That was just a copy of me.\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:553
msgid ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"A copy? Are you a ninja?\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:556
msgid ""
"{Natsume}\n"
"\"Hmm. It's kind of hard to do it in this world.\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:559
msgid "Then she looked over at the space next to her, and..."
msgstr ""

#: 40304:562
msgid ""
"{Natsume}\n"
"\"Come out.\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:563
msgid "She said."
msgstr ""

#: 40304:568
msgid ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"Wow!? There are two Natsume-chan?!\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:569
msgid "She really made a copy of herself! What is this?"
msgstr ""

#: 40304:570
msgid ""
"{Natsume}\n"
"\"It's Natsume.\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:571
msgid ""
"{Natsume'}\n"
"\"I am Natsume as well.\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:576
msgid ""
"{Amamiya}\n"
"\"This is... amazing.\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:577
msgid "Miya-san looked surprised as well. What the hell is going on here?"
msgstr ""

#: 40304:583
msgid ""
"{Natsume}\n"
"\"Man, we sure get sot in the hummer.\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:586
msgid ""
"{Natsume'}\n"
"\"I know, it's so dangerous this time of year.\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:589
msgid ""
"{Natsume}\n"
"\"Holy too!\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:592
msgid ""
"{Natsume'}\n"
"\"Pgyah!\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:593
msgid "...... It's so surreal."
msgstr ""

#: 40304:598
msgid ""
"{Amamiya}\n"
"\"Ah-hah-hah! Funny, so funny! You're great, Natsume!\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:599
msgid "Stupid parent."
msgstr ""

#: 40304:608
msgid ""
"{Natsume}\n"
"\"That was my copy. She'll do whatever I say.\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:609
msgid ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"I don't get it, but that sounds great.\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:610
msgid "It seemed convenient for classes and stuff."
msgstr ""

#: 40304:613
msgid ""
"{Natsume}\n"
"\"I was bored, being in that world all by myself, so I created her to play with. Until you came, Haruma.\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:614
msgid ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"I see.\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:615
msgid "I was so glad I found her, and that I was able to bring her back. It must have been so sad for her to spend her days like that."
msgstr ""

#: 40304:616
msgid ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"Let's do a lot of fun stuff everyday now!\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:619
msgid ""
"{Natsume}\n"
"\"Huh? It's kind of fun to have a stand-up comedy contest all by myself.\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:620
msgid ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"We'll do more fun stuff.\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:623
msgid ""
"{Natsume}\n"
"\"Yeah? If you want to, Haruma.\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:624
msgid "Yes. We should have more fun, to try and make up for her past. I have to show her more fun stuff."
msgstr ""

#: 40304:627
msgid ""
"{Natsume}\n"
"\"But I don't think Hisae will stay quiet.\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:628
msgid "Hisae - the principal."
msgstr ""

#: 40304:629
msgid ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"Do you think the principal will do something to you?\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:632
msgid ""
"{Natsume}\n"
"\"Maybe.\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:637
msgid ""
"{Amamiya}\n"
"\"Natsume-chan has interrupted her experiments twice so far.\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:638
msgid ""
"{Natsume}\n"
"\"The first time was when I ate the stone, and the second time was when I showed up in your experiment.\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:639
msgid ""
"{Amamiya}\n"
"\"Hisae-san was trying to create something different, but Natsume interrupted her with her copy. That's why Hisae-san wasn't able to finish what she was aiming for.\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:640
msgid ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"What was the principal trying to make?\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:643
msgid ""
"{Amamiya}\n"
"\"Well... I'm not sure about that.\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:644
msgid "Miya-san smiled and looked down. I thought he knew what it was, but he seemed like he didn't want me to ask him, so I didn't."
msgstr ""

#: 40304:645
msgid "I'm not sure why, but Natsume-chan kept interfering with the principal. Was the principal going to let go of her like this?"
msgstr ""

#: 40304:646
msgid "And the time we went to get Natsume-chan... That seemed way too easy, thinking back. I couldn't help but wonder if she was plotting something."
msgstr ""

#: 40304:647
msgid "I hope I'm just overreacting."
msgstr ""

#: 40304:650
msgid ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"Wow, look at the time.\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:651
msgid "The hands of the clock were pointing straight up. It's time to change the date."
msgstr ""

#: 40304:652
msgid ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"Well, I should be going.\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:653
msgid "I think I stayed too long. Natsume-chan pulled on my shirt as I stood up."
msgstr ""

#: 40304:656
msgid ""
"{Natsume}\n"
"\"Why don't you stay too, Haruma?\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:657
msgid "She said, with a straight face."
msgstr ""

#: 40304:658
msgid ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"Well, I don't think I should.\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:661
msgid ""
"{Natsume}\n"
"\"Why? Is it because you'll want to do something naughty if we sleep together?\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:665
msgid ""
"{Amamiya}\n"
"\"Pffft?!\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:666
msgid "Miya-san spat out his tea. How could you say such a thing in front of your own dad, Natsume-chan?"
msgstr ""

#: 40304:669
msgid ""
"{Amamiya}\n"
"\"H-Haruma-kun, are you--?\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:670
msgid ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"N-no I'm not! Don't take that seriously!\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:673
msgid ""
"{Amamiya}\n"
"\"O-okay. Of course, you wouldn't do that with her father around, right?\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:674
msgid ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"I wouldn't do that even if you weren't around!\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:678
msgid ""
"{Natsume}\n"
"\"Then what's the problem? We're just sleeping, so it doesn't matter where you sleep.\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:679
msgid ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"Well, it's not right.\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:682
msgid "*Cling*"
msgstr ""

#: 40304:685
msgid "But Natsume-chan wouldn't let me go. She kept looking at me with a lost expression."
msgstr ""

#: 40304:686
msgid ""
"{Natsume}\n"
"\"I don't know what to do with my dad when we're alone.\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:687
msgid "She whispered into my ears."
msgstr ""

#: 40304:688
msgid ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"Oh, I see.\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:689
msgid "Natsume-chan hadn't seen Miya-san since she was a little girl, and it's been about ten years. It might be little awkward to be alone with him."
msgstr ""

#: 40304:694
msgid ""
"{Amamiya}\n"
"\"Sure. If you don't mind, then why don't you stay, Haruma-kun?\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:695
msgid "Miya-san might have caught on about how Natsume-chan was feeling, and he asked me to stay as well. Maybe Miya-san was also feeling awkward."
msgstr ""

#: 40304:698
msgid ""
"{Natsume}\n"
"\"Let's all sleep together.\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:701
msgid ""
"{Amamiya}\n"
"\"I'll sleep in the middle. You and Natsume and can sleep on either side.\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:704
msgid ""
"{Natsume}\n"
"\"Then Haruma'll be too far from me!\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:707
msgid ""
"{Amamiya}\n"
"\"Well, just in case, you know?\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:708
msgid "They were both thinking that I was staying. But..."
msgstr ""

#: 40304:709
msgid ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"No, I can't. I didn't get permission from the dorm.\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:710
msgid "I really think I should go. They looked a little upset."
msgstr ""

#: 40304:713
msgid ""
"{Natsume}\n"
"\"Who cares about that!\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:716
msgid ""
"{Amamiya}\n"
"\"Don't worry about that. I'll explain to them if they ask.\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:717
msgid ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"But there are things you can't talk about with me around, right? I'm sure there's things you both want to talk about together.\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:720
msgid ""
"{Natsume}\n"
"\"That's the thing! I'm not sure what to talk about after all these years.\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:721
msgid ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"Don't worry about it. He's your father, and everything will turn out fine!!\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:722
msgid ""
"{Natsume}\n"
"\"But...\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:723
msgid "I'd never seen her so worried. I wished that I could stay close to her, but..."
msgstr ""

#: 40304:727
msgid ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"Don't think about anything. You just let Miya-san worry about it, and spoil yourself.\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:728
msgid "I'm sure we should let Miya-san handle this. They are father and daughter, after all."
msgstr ""

#: 40304:729
msgid ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"Right, Miya-san?\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:730
msgid "Miya-san swore to be a good father, so I was certain he could handle it."
msgstr ""

#: 40304:734
msgid ""
"{Amamiya}\n"
"\"Yeah, of course.\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:735
msgid "Miya-san nodded firmly, and softly stroked Natsume-chan's hair."
msgstr ""

#: 40304:740
msgid ""
"{Amamiya}\n"
"\"I just want you to stay. I'll take care of the thinking part, so don't worry about anything.\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:741
msgid "He stroked her hair softly. Natsume-chan closed her eyes like a cat, and let Miya-san do whatever he wanted."
msgstr ""

#: 40304:744
msgid ""
"{Natsume}\n"
"\"Alright. Haruma, you're in the way, go home.\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:745
msgid "She changed her mind instantly."
msgstr ""

#: 40304:746
msgid ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"Yeah, yeah, I'm leaving.\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:749
msgid ""
"{Natsume}\n"
"\"Hey, I'm just joking.\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:750
msgid ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"I know.\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:753
msgid "I smiled, and Natsume-chan's face went red as she turned away."
msgstr ""

#: 40304:754
msgid ""
"{Natsume}\n"
"\"I'll walk you out.\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:758
msgid ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"This is far enough.\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:761
msgid "I told her, as I walked out through the store. She was right behind me. Natsume-chan looked unhappy, but she nodded."
msgstr ""

#: 40304:762
msgid ""
"{Natsume}\n"
"\"Uh-huh. Alright.\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:763
msgid ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"Don't be so spoiled, okay? No, maybe you should?\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:766
msgid ""
"{Natsume}\n"
"\"I will. But I'm sleepy, so I'll go to bed soon.\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:767
msgid ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"I'm sure that's fine, too. Sleep tight.\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:768
msgid ""
"{Natsume}\n"
"\"Yeah, I will. You too.\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:769
msgid "She was stifling a yawn as we were talking. She really did seem sleepy."
msgstr ""

#: 40304:770
msgid ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"Well, I'll be going. Good night.\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:772
msgid "I waved at her and turned around."
msgstr ""

#: 40304:775
msgid ""
"{Natsume}\n"
"\"Hold on.\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:776
msgid "She grabbed onto my shirt once again as I started to walk."
msgstr ""

#: 40304:777
msgid ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"What?\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:780
msgid "I was attacked by something as I turned around. It was the shock of a small, soft pair of lips."
msgstr ""

#: 40304:783
msgid ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"Huh?\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:787
msgid "The lip parted ways with me in a moment. Natsume-chan was looking at me with a serious face."
msgstr ""

#: 40304:788
msgid ""
"{Natsume}\n"
"\"I thought I'd do it on your cheek, but you turned around so suddenly. Oh well.\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:789
msgid "You don't care? Well, I guess I don't mind, either. It made me happy."
msgstr ""

#: 40304:790
msgid ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"So, what was that for?\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:793
msgid ""
"{Natsume}\n"
"\"A good night kiss. You kissed me when I woke up, so we have to do it when I go to sleep, right?\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:794
msgid ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"Is that a rule?\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:797
msgid ""
"{Natsume}\n"
"\"Yes. I don't want to be unable to wake up again.\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:798
msgid ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"Oh...\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:799
msgid "Now it made sense. Natsume-chan woke up yesterday, and hadn't been back to sleep yet. But she was asleep for many years before that."
msgstr ""

#: 40304:800
msgid "Maybe she was still scared by the thought of not being able to wake up."
msgstr ""

#: 40304:801
msgid ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"Don't worry. If you can't get up, then I'll come to wake you up tomorrow.\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:804
msgid ""
"{Natsume}\n"
"\"Of course. You woke me up, so you have to keep waking me up. That's why I told you to stay tonight.\""
msgstr ""

#: 40304:805
msgid "I see. That was the reason she asked me to stay."
msgstr ""

#: 40304:806
msgid ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"I promise. I'll come to wake you up with my bike.\""
